picard.fingerprint

Class Fingerprint

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>

        • picard.fingerprint.Fingerprint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<HaplotypeBlock,HaplotypeProbabilities>, java.util.NavigableMap<HaplotypeBlock,HaplotypeProbabilities>, java.util.SortedMap<HaplotypeBlock,HaplotypeProbabilities>

    public class Fingerprint
extends java.util.TreeMap<HaplotypeBlock,HaplotypeProbabilities>
    class to represent a genetic fingerprint as a set of HaplotypeProbabilities objects that give the relative probabilities of each of the possible haplotypes at a locus.
